{
  "stem": "22174.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He had a car.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At that time, he had a car.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they drove in his car up to the German-Swiss border.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And before they came to the border, my sister got out of the car and took the train over to the German-Swiss border.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the other side of the border, she joined her fiance again in the car.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they came and visited me in Italy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they did the same thing on the way back home because [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they were not [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] allowed to have a relationship.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "A Jew and a Christ-- a non-Jew and a so-called Aryan were not allowed to have relationships, sexual relationships between men and women.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that was already against the law.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] just the funny thing about it is that he looked everything but German.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He had bright black hair, straight, but very black, real black hair.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he had a long hooked nose like they say the Jews have.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So he looked more Jewish than my sister did, or we did.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But they went for six years together.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But then, as I said, my parents [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] made my sister leave the country.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she got a visa, an immigration visa to England under the condition that she would work there as a house maid.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And so then they broke up their engagement, because he was not willing to leave the country.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because he had his career in the government, and he was much too German in all his ways.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "For him to live in another country would just been very difficult.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So they broke up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "The engagement broke up.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
